  "prompt": "What are the symptoms of chronic constipation?",
  "response": "Chronic constipation is characterized by infrequent or difficult bowel movements that persist for several weeks or longer. Common symptoms include:\n\n1. Fewer than three bowel movements per week.\n2. Hard or lumpy stools.\n3. Straining during bowel movements.\n4. Feeling of incomplete evacuation after a bowel movement.\n5. Feeling of blockage in the rectum.\n6. Needing to use manual maneuvers to pass stool, such as pressing on the abdomen or using a finger to remove stool from the rectum.\n7. Abdominal bloating or discomfort.\n\nIf you experience these symptoms regularly, it is important to consult with a healthcare provider for proper diagnosis and treatment.",
